  "prompt": "What is the proper way to use RSVP out of the following?",
  "response": "To provide proper guidance, I'll need to know the options you're deciding between. However, generally speaking, RSVP is an acronym derived from the French phrase \"R\u00e9pondez S'il Vous Pla\u00eet,\" which means \"Please respond.\" It's typically used in written invitations when the sender wants to know whether the invited person will attend the event. Here are some examples of its use:\n\n1. **Formal Invitation:** \n   - \"Please RSVP by [date].\"\n   - \"RSVP by October 15th to ensure your place at the event.\"\n\n2. **Informal Invitation:**\n   - \"Can you RSVP by Friday?\"\n   - \"Don't forget to RSVP!\"\n\nPlease provide the specific options you are considering, and I can help determine the best one for your context.",
